# Agent workspace: track reusable scaffold, ignore live state/artifacts.
# reports/ and archive/ (top-level and under scratch/) are deliberately NOT
# un-ignored here (polylogue-ocby): they previously carried `!` negations
# that forced entropic agent-run output (postmortems, retired
# devloop/scratch dumps) to be tracked in this PUBLIC repo. That content
# stays on disk (git rm --cached only, nothing deleted) but is no longer
# git-managed, and the negation is gone so new files there can't be
# re-tracked by a plain `git add`.
#
# scripts/ and tools/ got the same treatment (polylogue-kapb): the
# repo-tooling scripts that were actually referenced from hooks/docs moved
# into devtools/ as proper commands; the rest were either dead (deleted) or
# operator-personal convenience scripts (git rm --cached only, left on disk,
# no longer re-trackable by a plain `git add`).
.agent/*
!.agent/README.md
!.agent/CONVENTIONS.md
!.agent/handoffs/
!.agent/handoffs/**
!.agent/scratch/
.agent/scratch/*
!.agent/scratch/README.md

# Build metadata embedded into release artifacts
polylogue/_build_info.py
_site/

# Beads / Dolt files (added by bd init)
.dolt/
*.db
.beads-credential-key
